This paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it deals with automating diagnostic reasoning tasks using Bayesian networks. It may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it discusses Monte Carlo Markov chain sampling techniques. The paper's emphasis on distributed systems suggests it could also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on improving sampling techniques suggests it could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
